      "writtenOn": "2026-05-11T14:00:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I originally made this configurable per-threshold because different threshold levels may need different tolerance policies. For example, users may want to tolerate transient low/negative temperature readings, but still log upper critical temperature conditions as early as possible.\n\nFor misconfiguration prevention, would it make sense to enforce that within the same direction, a more severe level\u0027s ToleranceCount does not exceed that of a less severe one?",
      "parentUuid": "60e8d211_141fa5a7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1419,
        "startChar": 25,
        "endLine": 1419,
